This submittal updates our July 31, 2009 submittal and does not add any additional processes to our Risk Management Plan.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             INTRODUCTION TO RISK MANAGEMENT PLAN (RMP) REGULATED SUBSTANCES



Akzo Nobel Polymer Chemicals produces a variety of products at our Pasadena, Texas facility - an organic monomer for the lens manufacturing industry and organic peroxides for the plastic manufacturing industry.  The facility has three covered processes that use regulated chemicals above the applicability threshold: the organic monomer manufacturing process contains a diked allyl alcohol bulk storage tank (RMP toxic chemical); an organic peroxide manufacturing process contains a diked 2-methyl-1-butene bulk storage tank (RMP flammable chemical); and another organic peroxide manufacturing process utilizes a refrigerated building for drum storage of isopropyl chloroformate (RMP toxic chemical).



ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION and EMERGENCY RESPONSE POLICIES



Senior management is committed to chemical, employee, and plant safety at our facility.  Their commitment is demonstrated by:



       Maintaining a staff of onsite safety professionals to properly manage all aspects of safety;

       Providing a dedicated Safety Trainer for monthly employee training;

       Supporting the facility's Behavioral Based Safety Management System; 

